Module opentdk.api
Package org.opentdk.api.dispatcher

Class BaseDispatcher

java.lang.Object
org.opentdk.api.dispatcher.BaseDispatcher
Direct Known Subclasses:
EBaseSettings, EOperator
public class BaseDispatcher
extends Object
BaseDispatcher is build as a super class which can be inherited by subclasses to implement a list of variables, associated with any supported DataContainer classes. This BaseDispatcher provides all methods to create the associations between a dispatcher class and a DataContainer.

Settings class sample: 
 import org.opentdk.api.dispatcher.*;
 public class ESampleSettings extends BaseDispatcher{
        public static final BaseDispatchComponent MY_TITLE = new BaseDispatchComponent("Title", "/SampleSettings", "Sample Application");
        public static final BaseDispatchComponent MY_HOMEPATH = new BaseDispatchComponent("HomePath", "/SampleSettings", "/temp/sample");
 }
Author:
LK Test Solutions

    • getDataContainer

      public static DataContainer getDataContainer​(String dispatcherClassName)
      Returns a DataContainer that is assigned to the extended sub class of BaseDispatcher, where the BaseDispatchComponent variables are declared.

       Usage samples:
 1.) get DataContainer from dispatcher class which extends BaseDispatcher - no inherited BaseDispatchComponent declarations
        ECustomSettings.getDataContainer(ECustomSettings.class.getSimpleName());
 2.) get DataContainer from dispatcher class which extends EBaseSettings - with inherited BaseDispatchComponent declarations
        EChessAppSettings.getDataContainer(EBaseSettings.class.getSimpleName());
      Parameters:
      dispatcherClassName - The simple name of the dispatcher class where the BaseDispatchComponent variables are declared. In case the dispatcher class extends a super class with inherited declarations of BaseDispatchComponent, then the simple name of the super class needs to be used. This will not effect the super class BaseDispatcher(), because BaseDispatcher does not include declarations of BaseDispatchComponent.
      Returns:
      object of type DataContainer

    • setDataContainer

      public static void setDataContainer​(Class<?> dispatcherClass, String dispatcherFile)
      Assigns a DataContainer to the BaseDispatchComponent variables that are declared in an extended sub class of BaseDispatcher. The DataContainer acts as a runtime storage for the values of the BaseDispatchComponent variables and is linked to the defined file which acts as the permanent storage for the DataContainer.
      Parameters:
      dispatcherClass - - the dispatcher class where the variables of type BaseDispatchComponent are declared
      dispatcherFile - - full path and name of the file that stores the values of BaseDispatchComponent variables which are defined within the dispatcher class

    • setDataContainer

      public static void setDataContainer​(Class<?> dispatcherClass, String dispatcherFile, String rootNode)
      Assigns a DataContainer to the BaseDispatchComponent variables that are declared in an extended sub class of BaseDispatcher. The DataContainer acts as a runtime storage for the values of the BaseDispatchComponent variables that is linked to the defined file, which acts as the permanent storage for the DataContainer. This method will also check if the root node of tree formatted file matches with the root node defined within the corresponding dispatcher class.
      Parameters:
      dispatcherClass - - the dispatcher class where the variables of type BaseDispatchComponent are declared
      dispatcherFile - - full path and name of the file that stores the values of BaseDispatchComponent variables which are defined within the dispatcher class
      rootNode - - name of the root node within the tree formated file, used to check if the content of the file matches to the dispatcher class

    • setDataContainer

      public static void setDataContainer​(Class<?> dispatcherClass, DataContainer dc)
      Assigns a DataContainer to the BaseDispatchComponent variables that are declared in an extended sub class of BaseDispatcher. The DataContainer acts as a runtime storage for the values of the BaseDispatchComponent variables.
      Parameters:
      dispatcherClass - - the dispatcher class where the variables of type BaseDispatchComponent are declared
      dc - - DataContainer instance, representing the runtime storage for values of the BaseDispatchComponent variables

      dc - - DataContainer instance, representing the runtime storage for values of the BaseDispatchComponent variables

    • setDataContainer

      public static void setDataContainer​(Class<?> dispatcherClass, InputStream inStream)
      Assigns a DataContainer to the BaseDispatchComponent variables that are declared in an extended sub class of BaseDispatcher. The DataContainer will be initialized with the contend of an InputStream and acts as a runtime storage for the values of the BaseDispatchComponent variables.
      Parameters:
      dispatcherClass - - the dispatcher class where the variables of type BaseDispatchComponent are declared
      inStream - - InputStream with text content that will be linked to the BaseDispatchComponent variables
